column5: We did the Chocolate Moose. It was fine but really busy. The quit serving breakfast at 11 and we got there at 11:20. No exceptions, so we had to eat lunch. Food was decent. Hooks
Harbourage Cafe on the Canada side has real good breakfast.
Good food, service, and prices. However, you can have a long wait on some days. In the Falls the Chocolate Moose is good. Too bad the Cafe closed.

Hey, give "The Library" a try. It's by Super One & the movie threater. . . where the Mexican restaurant used to be. Great coffee, great food. Open at 5:00 am every day as I recall. Parking lot WILL fit your vehicle and boat. Parking lot needs some patching so go slow. Hours may reduce when fall/winter sets in. Say 'hi' the Brook and her friendly staff. We're up here for our annual 5 month visit and try to support all the locally owned and operated places.
On hwy 35 north,breakfast in willow river dave's cafe,5 guys had coffee n great breakfast,, about 37 dollars,place opens at 8 every table was full at 7:55

Looking for options Shorelunch Cafe closed some years ago, and now Sandy's Place owners have retired and closed. What's left for a morning breakfast stop around 7:30-8 am in International Falls on a weekday?
Chocolate Moose or Voyageur are good options, Moose opens at 6am, Voy at 8am
In addition.... McDonalds Dunkin Donuts There is a coffee joint downtown, I think they serve breakfast Thunderbird Lodge I think Sha Sha also does breakfast
Always liked the Shorelunch Cafe. Too bad they closed.
If you cross to FF there is a little place by Rainy Lake Sports that serves a nice breakfast...if you are going east
Just stop in Orr at T Pattenns cafe !
If going through Dryden, stop at the Patricia Inn! Good breakfasts. Sent from my iPad using Tapatalk
Is VFW doing breakfast any more?
I don't know. I've never been in there.
